cs.GT, cs.EC, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.IT. 

The paper deals with game theory, mechanism design, and inequality, which are all topics that fall under the category of cs.GT (Game Theory and Mechanism Design). The use of tolls to incentivize socially desirable behavior falls under the category of cs.EC (Economics and Computation). The analysis of wealth distribution and income elasticity of travel time falls under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The use of novel measures to quantify inequality falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the discussion of theories of justice falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory).
